Heat a small frying pan and add 1 tablespoon of oil.  Once hot add the onion and cook until soft. Place all the kofta ingredients, apart from the oil, into a bowl and mix thoroughly. Shape into sausage shapes.Heat a heavy flat griddle pan. Oil the koftas with the remaining oil and cook on the griddle for 6-7 minutes turning around constantly so they cook evenly.Mix all the dressing ingredients in a bowl and season to taste with salt and pepper.To serve, stuff the pitta bread with the cooked koftas, dressing and cheese and enjoy warm.